By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria exceeded 100,000 with the additional 1,024 fresh infections recorded on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. The report released by the health agency via it’s twitter account has it that Lagos State alone recorded 653 fresh infections in the day under review while the other 16 states (including the FCT) where new cases were reported accounted for the remaining 371 cases as follows: Plateau-63Benue-48Zamfara-45FCT-42Rivers-27Ondo-26Adamawa-26Kaduna-22Edo-18Ogun-16Imo-12Kano-9Yobe-6Ekiti-5Jigawa-4Osun-2. According to the report, the total confirmed cases have risen to 100,087 out of which80,030 patients have been treated and discharged from various isolation facilities in Nigeria. The NCDC further added that 1,358 lives had been lost to COVID-19 related complications since the index case was reported in February 2020 in the country. See the states breakdown of total confirmed cases as reported by the health agency below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Again, Lagos State Wednesday led the COVID-19 table with 85 cases as Nigeria recorded 155 fresh infections, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. The report released by the NCDC via it's twitter handle further revealed that the fresh cases were recorded… November 5, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control said the COVID-19 death toll in Nigeria has risen to 1, 163 as 152 fresh cases of the novel virus were reported on Wednesday. The report released via twitter handle listed the states that recorded the infections… November 18, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Nigeria's epicentre of COVID-19, Lagos State, accounted for 84 out of 155 fresh cases of recorded on Wednesday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has said. According the report released by the NCDC via it's twitter handle